<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04725</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT RECOGNIZING TRANSPORTATION NETWORK COMPANIES, PRESCRIBING REQUIREMENTS, GUIDELINES AND STANDARDS FOR THEIR OPERATION, PROVIDING PENALTIES FOR VIOLATION THEREOF</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Defines TNC as an organization, whether a corporation, partnership, or sole proprietorship 
operating in the Philippines, that provides pre-arranged transportation services for compensation 
using an internet-based application or digital platform technology to connect passengers and 
drivers using their personal vehicles.

Highlights several provisions as regards to regulation (application/renewal for permit); operation (requirements, zero tolerance for drug or alcohol use, vehicle safety policy, fare setting and disclosures, electronic receipt provisions, drivers and vehicles identification, confidentiality of passenger's information, requirements for and status of drivers as independent contractors, 
insurance requirements, street hails prohibition, acceptance of excess cash payments, fleet service 
ownership, tax treatment); and enforcement of this Act.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASTELO, PRECIOUS HIPOLITO</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-20</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORTATION ON 2019-09-24</td></tr></table>